text.tspan: Annual number of suicides and homicides per 100,000 people. Suicide deaths are underreported in many
countries due to social stigma and cultural or legal concerns. This data is adjusted for this underreporting
to estimate the actual rate of suicides.
Data source: WHO, Global Health Observatory (2022); United Nations Office on Drugs and Crime (2022)
Note: To allow for comparisons between countries and over time, this metric is age-standardized.
